John Alechenu Political differences were set aside as chieftains of the ruling All Progressives Congress and those of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party attended the wedding of the son of the PDP presidential candidate in the 2019 general elections, Atiku Abubakar, and the daughter of a former Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, Nuhu Ribadu. The Muslim wedding which took place in Asokoro, Abuja, on Saturday, had in attendance the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, pioneer National Chairman of the APC, Chief Bisi Akande, and the caretaker National chairman of the APC, Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State and his  Kano and Kaduna state counterparts, Abdullahi Ganduje and Nasir El-Rufai respectively. Former Kano State governor, Rabiu Kwankwaso who is a chieftain of the PDP was also in attendance. The father of the bride is currently a chieftain of the APC. Expressing his gratitude to all who attended the event, Atiku in a tweet on his verified twitter handle @atiku wrote: “On behalf of my family, I thank those present and also well-wishers for their prayers at the wedding Fatiha of my dear son, @HHMustaphaAA and his wife, Afrah El-Nafaty. May Allah bless you all for making it a truly special day for me and my family.” Copyright PUNCH.
